There is something I want to talk you about.

And as often, it is a consideration that came from you. I was at a meet-up, and we were talking about the body positive movement. And one of you stood up to say ¬´¬†We should not even be body positive - we should be body neutral¬†¬ª.
Body neutral. Stop considering ourselves through the lens of our body, and physical appearance.
I thought about it. And I found it incredibly right. The body positive movement is great because it allowed to celebrate body diversity. It allowed to see real and raw where we used to see staged and airbrushed. But fact is, it still comes down to our bodies. When we are so much more than that.
Think about why your appreciate your loved ones. Is it for the way they look ? Or is it for who they are as a person ? This is where we should focus our energy. On who we are, rather than on how we look üí´
